The paper discusses the manipulation of bibliometric indicators using false papers uploaded to an institutional web domain. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the detection of citation counting manipulation, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
